Check before run
================

* Check where is your mesh file
* Check what version of openmpi (or other MPI library) you are using

Notes
=====

* External forces and Young modulus are rescaled by factor 1e-8.
* Griffith energy for graphite is 200 * 1e-8 for units consistency.

Example run
===========

1) Calculation of stress intensity factor K1

* Calculation of Griffith energy and SIF for mode K1.
* Calculate problem for three approximation orders, i.e. 1 (linear), 2 (quadratic), 3 (cubic).
* Calculate problem for three refinement levels (in proximity of crack front).

* convergence_study.sh NAME_OF_SCRIPT
* -f NAME_OF_FILE 
* -l VALUE_OF_LOAD_FACTOR 
* -g REFERENCE_GRIFFITH_ENERGY 
* -o APPROX_ORDERS_SEPARATED_BY_COMMAS 
* -r REFINEMENT_LEVELS_SEPARATED_BY_COMMAS

./convergence_study.sh -f T3_horiz_assym.cub -l -1 -g 2e-6 -o 3 -r 2 -d 3pb_assym

2) Calculation of crack propagation

* Crack propagation as an input file uses previously obtained solution from step (1)
* Note that linear elements (1st order) have sheer locking, and usually give overstiff solution

* out_spatial_2_1.h5m - this is 2-order 1-refinement_level
./arc_length.sh -f 3pb_assym/out_spatial_3_2.h5m -a 1e-5 -n 80 -g 2e-6 -d crack_propagation

3) Plotting

* check that you have installed awk and grep
* copy and paste to line command:
echo "0 0" | tee load_path_DispY_vs_Lambda && awk '/load_path_disp ent 108 dim 1/ {print -$13,-$15}' crack_propagation/log | tee -a load_path_DispY_vs_Lambda

* Wher DIRNAME for example is
DIRNAME=material_forces_T3_horiz_DATE-2013-12-16_TIME_16_32_31

or short version,

grep "load_path:" arc_length_out_spatial_1_1_DATE-2013-12-16_TIME_16_36_03/log
grep "load_path_disp ent 383 dim 1"  arc_length_out_spatial_1_1_DATE-2013-12-16_TIME_16_36_03/log

